 TWO siblings abducted at gunpoint in Abakaliki, the Ebonyi State capital, have been rescued by police, spokesperson for the state command Loveth Odah told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) yesterday. Odah said the kidnappers robbed the mother of the siblings of a huge amount of money before abducting her children. She said the kidnappers demanded N10 million ransom but had to abandon the children at a location in Afikpo South Local Government Area of the state. 